{
  "id": "c-mo1uw2ml-33fceb4a9943",
  "goal": "Should the patron approve decisions before they're made, or ratify them after?",
  "status": "concluded",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-16T19:12:17.229Z",
  "parentId": "c-mo1mq93f-a8d85ce47baf",
  "createdSessionId": "e2eab8bf-426b-4dd3-9c10-ddae870e8271",
  "conclusion": "Ratify after. System proceeds on best guess; surfaces Tier 4 decisions asynchronously with tradeoffs pre-articulated and a default already applied. Sean's sharpest framing: 'Requiring input should be akin to an incident in other systems, a real failure.' This reframes patron interaction from blocking approval to post-hoc ratification. Decision taken in design session 860f69d7. Original quest body: docs/archive/quests/w-mo0v636y-41c8aeff857f.json.",
