{
  "id": "c-mo1uw4qd-c1ba2be4eaf8",
  "goal": "Should the Astrolabe task manifest end with a mandatory terminal verify task?",
  "status": "dropped",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-16T19:12:19.957Z",
  "parentId": "c-mo1mq93f-a8d85ce47baf",
  "createdSessionId": "e2eab8bf-426b-4dd3-9c10-ddae870e8271",
  "conclusion": "No. Originally the manifest ended with a verify-only task to force final validation. Dropped because it blocks the anima from freely appending new tasks to the end via piece-add — a mandatory tail breaks append semantics. Final verification is an engine loop property (the implement engine runs verify against the whole mandate), not a manifest structure requirement. Decision taken during v1 commission w-mo0ypqs4. Original quest body: docs/archive/quests/w-mo0v636y-41c8aeff857f.json.",
